Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveEnugu’s former First Lady Clara, married to former Gov. Sullivan Chime has remarried.
She got married on Friday, April 29, at Amuda Isuochi, Umunneochi LGA in Abia state.
The bridegroom is said to be a northern Christian from Kaduna.
Clara remarried 10 years after her previous marriage ended with Sullivan.
The news of their rocky marriage broke out towards the end of the governor’s second term.
The administration then claimed Clara was not mentally stable, the reason her husband locked her u for medical attention.
But Clara insisted she had been enduring domestic violence in the marriage, ad her attempt tp cry out was stifled.
